          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-11 12:50:31" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to receive and show hospitality to a stranger, that is, someone who is not regarded as a member of the extended family or a close friend</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to show hospitality</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to receive a stranger as a guest</Gloss>
                <Gloss>hospitality</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>To receive a stranger as a guest is sometimes expressed idiomatically as ‘to let a stranger sit at one’s table,’ ‘to offer a bed to a stranger,’ or ‘to let a stranger enter one’s house.’</Comments>
